com.comfortanalytics.aon

Class Aobj

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.comfortanalytics.aon.Aobj
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Agroup

    public abstract class Aobj
extends java.lang.Object
    Base representation for all Aon data types. Use Alist and Amap to create data structures.

    Be aware that when encoding/decoding, if the underlying format (such as JSON) doesn't provide a mechanism to differentiate between data types (such as numbers), values might not decode as the same type they were encoded.

      • toBoolean

        public boolean toBoolean()
        Attempts to return a boolean value. Numerics will return false for 0 and true for anything else. Strings should return true for "true" or "1" and false for "false" or "0". Anything else will throws a ClassCastException.
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassCastException - If not convertible.

      • toDouble

        public double toDouble()
        Attempts to return a double value. Numerics of other types will cast the results. Booleans will return 0 for false and 1 for true. Strings will attempt to parse the numeric which may result in a parse exception. Anything else will throw a ClassCastException.
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassCastException - If not convertible.
